               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330103-30-person389">
                  ROBERT 
                  HUGHES
               <interp inst="t18330103-30-person389" type="surname" value="HUGHES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330103-30-person389" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330103-30-person389" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Phoenix-street, Somer's-town, and am a broker. On the 27th of December the prisoner came to my shop, and offered me a lock for sale - having heard some inquiry about it, I said I should send for an officer; he ran off - I pursued, but could not stop him: but I saw this pair of bellows taken from under his arm - they were taken to my shop, and I gave them and the lock to the officer; he told me where he lived, and we found him behind a palliasse at his father's - his father denied his being at home.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330103-30-person390">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COX
               <interp inst="t18330103-30-person390" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330103-30-person390" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330103-30-person390" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable S 78). I produce the bellows, which I received from Hughes - I went with him to apprehend the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330103-30-person391">
                  JOHN 
                  BOSWORTH
               <interp inst="t18330103-30-person391" type="surname" value="BOSWORTH"></interp>
