            . I live in <placeName id="t18330103-30-crimeloc176">Seymour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330103-30-crimeloc176" type="placeName" value="Seymour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330103-30-crimeloc176" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330103-30-off174 t18330103-30-crimeloc176"></join>, and <rs id="t18330103-30-viclabel177" type="occupation">keep a toy-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330103-30-victim388 t18330103-30-viclabel177"></join>. These are my bellows - I did not miss them till they were brought to me; I had seen them safe that day in my shop - I do not remember seeing the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was never in his shop - my brother picked up the lock, and asked me to sell it; I went with it, and met a boy who I knew, who asked me to sell the bellows, and he would give me 2d. or 3d. - I went to sell the lock and could not; I ran off, and a man took the bellows from under my arm.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM COX. When I found the prisoner concealed, as has been stated, I said I wanted him concerning a lock he said, "My father gave me the lock;" but his father who was there, said he knew nothing about it - I then asked the prisoner if he had offered a pair of bellows - he said he knew nothing about them; but afterwards he said, "Be as favourable as you can to me, I will tell you the truth," and he showed me the shop where he offered them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18330103-30-verdict178" type="verdictDescription">
